div.p: Module: url-shortener-m3 outbox/poller.go Coordinator: 1 goroutine Workers: 3 goroutines Channel buffer: 50

ILLEGAL TRANSITION Calling MarkPublished(entry.ID) BEFORE publisher.Publish() succeeds
Consequence: Row marked published but event never reached broker. Silent data loss analytics-service and notification-service never see event.
Enforced by: sequential Publish MarkPublished ordering in outboxWorker

ul.li: Partial index: WHERE published_at IS NULL
Coordinator blocks on jobChan <- entry if all 3 workers are busy (backpressure)
sync.Mutex in amqpPublisher.Publish serializes concurrent AMQP writes
Workers are independent: one RABBITMQ_DOWN does not block others
Graceful shutdown: workers drain jobChan before exiting (range closes)

div.p: IDLE Invariant: timer armed (2s) jobChan may hold pending items No DB connection held
QUERYING FetchUnpublished(ctx, 50) Pool conn acquired WHERE published_at IS NULL ORDER BY created_at ASC LIMIT 50
FANNING_OUT Range over fetched entries jobChan <- entry (blocks if full) Backpressure from workers
STOPPING close(jobChan) Workers drain remaining items Goroutine exits
WAITING for entry := range jobChan Goroutine parked (no CPU) Unblocked by coordinator send
PUBLISHING publisher.Publish(ctx, entry.EventType, entry.Payload) Exchange: url-shortener (topic) DeliveryMode: Persistent sync.Mutex held on AMQP channel
MARKING_DONE outboxRepo.MarkPublished(ctx, entry.ID) UPDATE outbox SET published_at = now() WHERE id = $1 Pool conn acquired + released
RABBITMQ_DOWN publisher.Publish returned error Row NOT marked published Will be re-fetched next poll cycle log.Warn event_id
MARK_FAILED MarkPublished returned error Event WAS published to broker Row re-fetched re-published Consumer must be idempotent log.Error event_id
EXITING jobChan closed by coordinator range loop terminates Goroutine exits cleanly
